race.comment: Open race to close out the card. WOODSTOCK ROCK (5) finished just a head from the winner in second last start over 1100m at this track after racing handy. Best figures measure up and is sure to run well. DEVIL DEVIL (2) progressed nicely last time out when he worked home well to finish just 1.4 lengths from the winner in third over 1050m at Rockhampton. Ryan Wiggins gets the best out of this five-year-old gelding and will prove hard to beat in this suitable race. OUR TURN NOW (4) turned in a strong run last time at the first run of the prep when he settled well back before running on hard to be beaten only a nose into second over 1400m at Rockhampton. Will be running on late again. SCRUB CHAIN (3) finished sixth over 1609m at Townsville at his most recent appearance on August 9. Makes plenty of appeal while fresh.
